'''22 point regulation''' was a guideline approved by the [[Communist Party of China]] in 1988 to encourage [[Taiwan]]ese investments in the [[People's Republic of China]].

==Focus==
The law encouraged specifically land production and land development in [[Hainan Island]], [[Guangdong]], [[Fujian]] and other coastal provinces. It guaranteed Taiwan establishments would not be nationalized, and that exports were free from [[tariffs]]. Taiwanese management would be granted multiple [[Visa (document)|visas]].

